<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Register group for timer configurations related to EEE of 10G Base-R PCS
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
These timer value are used by the 64-bit PMA clocks in 10G-Base-R PCS (IEEE 802.3, clause 49)

PMA Clock frequency = ~161.13 Mhz (= ((((66/64)/64) x 10 GHz)) = ((660000/(64 x 64)) MHz))
PMA Clock time-period = 1/PMA Clock Frequency = ~6.2 ns (= ((64x64)/660) ns)
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
One micro-second timer configuration register
------------------------------
<reg_public_text>:
This register value is used to elaps 1us time as specified in IEEE802.3az-2010 clause 49.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
This holds number of 64-bit PMA clocks required to achieve 1 micro-second (1 us) time interval.

As per IEEE 803.3az-2010, min and max values are as follows:

MIN : 1.1 us = 178
MAX: 1.3 us = 209

Note: Default value is ~1.1 us = 178
------------------------------
